Every now and then, I have to remind the five felines in the family about the necessity for acceptance in a household as diverse as ours. I have been explaining to them – for more than two years – that they have to share the house with my dog, Charles. The progress has been slow. Even though Charles is an adorable, cuddly 50kg puppy, the cats still terrorise him at times because, well, they can. Cat owners will understand. So, last week I called a family meeting again, sat the cats down, again, and gave them the diversity speech, again....